{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bd1d12d6-6dfc-491d-9545-83513875cf71","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0 dropped the VSTest adapter by default.** That's why `vstest.console` can't discover your tests.\n\nIn 3.x, the VSTest bridge was included automatically, so `vstest.console` worked. Starting with 4.0, the default runner is **Microsoft Testing Platform** — test projects build as standalone executables and no longer ship the VSTest adapter.\n\n### Your options\n\n**Option A — Migrate off `vstest.console`** (recommended):\nUse `dotnet test` or run the test executable directly:\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n# or\n./bin/Debug/net8.0/TestProject\n```\n\n**Option B — Re-enable VSTest compatibility:**\nAdd this property to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingExtensionsProfile>AllMicrosoft</TestingExtensionsProfile>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis brings back the VSTest bridge adapter so `vstest.console` can discover tests again.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"848094cf-bfbd-4217-a6d0-6d988dcb6341","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the breaking change between MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 and 4.1.0. I know about this change:\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the default test runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft Testing Platform (the new `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`). In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, even though Microsoft.Testing.Platform was available, the default was still VSTest-compatible, meaning `vstest.console` could discover and run tests.\n\nIn MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the default runner is Microsoft Testing Platform, and VSTest support is no longer included by default. \n\nNow I'm looking at the practical implications: `vstest.console.exe` can't find tests anymore because the project no longer generates a VSTest-compatible adapter. To fix this, I can either enable dotnet test support with a property flag, switch to the MSTest runner directly, or restore VSTest compatibility by generating the adapter again. So the core issue is that MSTest.Sdk 4.0 switched to Microsoft Testing Platform by default, which means `vstest.console` can't find the tests anymore since there's no VSTest adapter included. I can either recommend migrating to `dotnet test` or adding `<TestingExtensionsProfile>AllMicrosoft</TestingExtensionsProfile>` to restore VSTest compatibility.","outputTokens":900,"requestId":"0C00:3B8D06:6E43C26:77BE25B:69F02445"},"id":"1e23df9b-02d9-4e5f-8ddf-ef79c1e37dc2","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:07:04.996Z","parentId":"6bc29075-c2ea-4275-94e7-fc0fe14ea315"}
